LAGOS , February 5 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The Economic Community of West African States -LRB- ECOWAS -RRB- Committee of Five on Sierra Leone , headed by Nigerian Foreign Minister Tom Ikimi , is now in New York to brief the United Nations Security Council on the situation in S. Leone .
During the trip , Nigerian head of state General Sani Abacha , who is also ECOWAS chairman , and the committee will brief the council on the progress made so far for a peaceful resolution of the crisis in S. Leone .
The committee , composed of Nigeria , Ghana , Guinea , Cote d 'Ivoire and Liberia , will be joined in New York by representatives of the Organization of African Unity and ECOWAS secretariat .
It is expected to discuss with U.N. Secretary - General Kofi Annan and the Security Council on the need for the deployment of a U.N. observer mission to facilitate the disarmament of combatants as outlined in the peace plan signed last October in Conakry , Guinea .
A foreign ministry statement disclosed on Wednesday that the discussions will also focus on strategies for harmonizing the efforts of some members of the international community which have pledged cooperation with ECOWAS and the council with a view to restoring constitutional order in Sierra Leone .
Under the Conakry peace plan , the ruling military junta , which seized power in a coup on May 25 last year , will hand over power to ousted President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah on April 22 this year .
The junta , which signed the peace accord , said later , however , the timetable was unrealistic due to the delay in the disarmament exercise scheduled to begin last December .
A U.N. fact-finding team has recently concluded a three-day visit to Sierra Leone , reportedly to pave the way for the deployment of U.N. military observer mission in that troubled country .
